title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18 §§ 358-2.8 - Commissioner
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18 §§ 358-2.8 - Commissioner

State Regulations

Commissioner means the New York State Commissioner of

Temporary and Disability Assistance, or the Commissioner of Health or the

Commissioner of the Office of Children and Family Services, depending upon the
type of hearing involved as set forth in section
358-2.30
of this Part, or their
designees. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 18
§§
358-2.8

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
